    "keyframes": [
        {
            "Text": "Each light on the map represents a heat signal (for example, a fire) that is visible from an infrared satellite in space. The timeline shows data from 2015.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":73.88573458195845,"lng":-158.4408981514672},"sw":{"lat":-52.52299231514463,"lng":169.65089024780585}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "StartFrame": "2015-04-01",
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "In Africa, seasonal crop burning is visible through sweeping fires. This common agricultural technique allows soil to regain nutrients for the next growing season. Notice the crop burning fires in the middle and lower half of the continent.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":55.973611032181516,"lng":-97.26372326956887},"sw":{"lat":-46.243161338047734,"lng":129.30345413711572}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "Fires from oil extraction burn in Egypt, Libya, Algeria, and the Middle East. Oil fields produce methane along with crude oil. The gas is often burned, or \"flared\" on the spot when it cannot be recovered or pipelined, resulting in a consistent flame.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":47.14119311321615,"lng":-5.373883938156126},"sw":{"lat":8.913287631201014,"lng":78.81265433301658}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "The fires in North Dakota and Texas are also a result of flaring. In this case, resources are extracted using hydraulic fracturing, a process in which large explosions are triggered deep within rock formations to fracture the shale beds. A mixture of water, sand, and chemicals is then pumped into the pipeline to widen the fractures to extract oil or gas.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":54.17951535208853,"lng":-131.2652514276748},"sw":{"lat":24.493882035313515,"lng":-56.87802621126659}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "The Bakken Shale formation in North Dakota is one of the top oil-producing regions in the United States. Like the previous oil sites, it also produces gas. In 2014, over 25% of the extracted gas was flared. State regulations have since helped decrease this number to under 10% by 2016. The number has since been on the rise.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":51.79044232846596,"lng":-112.65714230827193},"sw":{"lat":43.05806197685102,"lng":-88.23410213655207}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "A note for Pittsburgh residents: Nearly a quarter of North Dakota's oil travels through Pittsburgh on long oil trains before reaching a refinement plant in Philadelphia.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":51.79044232846596,"lng":-112.65714230827193},"sw":{"lat":43.05806197685102,"lng":-88.23410213655207}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "In California, forest fires are becoming more prevalent as a result of warmer, drier summers with little rainfall. Notice the bright flashes of light, which represent these fires.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":42.73466859375439,"lng":-133.00747992147862},"sw":{"lat":31.057874672431897,"lng":-105.36709946457522}
            },
            "Pause": false,
            "Layers": [
                "show-viirs"
            ],
            "Map": "dark-base"
        },
        {
            "Text": "Wildfires in Indonesia destroyed over 6.4 million acres of forest from June to October 2015, causing an air pollution crisis. The expansion of palm oil plantations and conversion and draining of peatland contributed to the intensity of haze from the fires.",
            "BoundingBox": {
                "ne":{"lat":9.77890318744266,"lng":82.82748412788706},"sw":{"lat":-10.069828090516134,"lng":120.45194077842817}
            },
